  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Food Assistance and Nutrition Support to Conflict Affected Families in Borno State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Despite expanding humanitarian presence in Northeast Nigeria, over 5.2 million people face Crisis or Emergency levels of food insecurity (Food Security Cluster.  In newly accessible parts of Borno, &quot;current Global Acute Malnutrition (GAM) rates range from 20 to 50%, reflecting an `Extreme Critical&apos; situation [and] 87% of people in newly accessible areas are completely dependent on food distribution, which has been inadequate.

This action will support conflict-affected families, including IDPs, returnees and host communities to meet basic, emergency food and nutritional needs. CAFOD in partnership with Catholic Relief Services (CRS) and North East Youth Initiative for Development (NEYIF) (together the &quot;implementing partners&quot; or IPs) will meet the immediate survival needs of vulnerable families in Gubio and Magumeri Local Government Authorities (LGAs) in Borno State, over a 9-month period through integrated, mutually reinforcing food assistance and nutrition interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
